<subSubSection id="C463BED86C6E885F6F72580A46342353" pageId="525" pageNumber="526" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="01A49C583D0BB343B9E392F5FBA817BD" pageId="525" pageNumber="526">
<taxonomicName id="9206A01815BD876FBF79417419CFCFB5" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Leptoferonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="525" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Leptoferonia</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 321, 336. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="90EF8C8313D6131B99754874EBE5004D" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="525" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis id="376D18F425C4AF058E1121356C131780" italics="true" pageId="525" pageNumber="526">Feronia angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1828 by original designation. Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="0AB3FD4307D72E410404E370AEEF9777" italics="true" pageId="525" pageNumber="526">leptos</emphasis>
(thin, slender) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="69CDFB9C196EF84037BEF4664F64817F" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="525" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="96922BCD0F06C2A1CD3D60E012D22902" italics="true" pageId="525" pageNumber="526">Feronia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="58ADEB3325902146988F5188127B30D9" italics="true" pageId="525" pageNumber="526">q.v</emphasis>
.], alluding to the slender shape of adults of these 
<taxonomicName id="3FD3931CCF5F8EAAEAE71BEED0EC4EE2" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="525" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CDEFEB40D8E836369CAA4CF4AB8C4C9" italics="true" pageId="525" pageNumber="526">Feronia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="3883D2F64DDE22798C170977755E4BC6" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="525" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="568C4FC717BCDB82D155C12F31FB4F76" italics="true" pageId="525" pageNumber="526">Pterostichus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) species [feminine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FFADC5655C3E2225658C37A15EA5EB46" pageId="526" pageNumber="527" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="2BB7B842F8E810635EA8A30E52A174DD" pageId="526" pageNumber="527">
<pageBreakToken id="57038FFE3E0BC589F7390293BB0EEA65" pageId="526" pageNumber="527" start="start">Diversity</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="080345D9F9EB497436FD183C7DE8CDE4" pageId="526" pageNumber="527">Twenty-six species in western North America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1DF6791D3B53CB7D33AB7D79DFCBD13C" pageId="526" pageNumber="527" type="identification">
<paragraph id="842FA062462557B90036DAB4F2F94E3C" pageId="526" pageNumber="527">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4B54AA5B49B7CD1569DE886E86F56A65" pageId="526" pageNumber="527">
Hacker (1968) revised the species. Since then, four new species have been described by Will (2007), one species (
<taxonomicName id="3D1450FEE31B802E2AE31FD4964FF1AC" baseAuthorityName="Hatch" baseAuthorityYear="1951" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="526" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rothi">
<emphasis id="045A84FBE90AB13927E0735066C636C4" italics="true" pageId="526" pageNumber="527">Pterostichus rothi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) has been transferred from 
<taxonomicName id="221DB3573420EBC41E994CDB414F4322" authorityName="Van Dyke" authorityYear="1926" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anilloferonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="526" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4AA1FF17EFC9FF47895DD584295FCD44" italics="true" pageId="526" pageNumber="527">Anilloferonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to this subgenus (Will 2007), and one subspecies (
<taxonomicName id="A5138CCA1D47A424A5999406040F3B49" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="526" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="stapedius" subSpecies="yosemitensis">
<emphasis id="DC46929186FB1723521DB64BB8590A6E" italics="true" pageId="526" pageNumber="527">Pterostichus stapedius yosemitensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) has been raised to species level by Bousquet (1999: 164).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
